Germany Stays Perfect in Euro 2012 Soccer Qualifying; Italy, Croatia Win

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-06-03T21:50:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-03/germany-remains-perfect-in-euro-2012-soccer-qualifying-italy-croatia-win.html
Germany  maintained its perfect record
in qualifying for soccer’s 2012 European Championship. Italy and
Croatia also won.  Mario Gomez scored both goals, including the winner in the
final minute, as Germany beat Austria 2-1 in Vienna. Germany’s
sixth straight win moved it seven points ahead of Belgium, which
tied 1-1 with Turkey in Group A. Kazakhstan beat Azerbaijan 2-1
in the final group game.  Giuseppe Rossi, Antonio Cassano and Giampaolo Pazzini
scored to lead Italy past Estonia 3-0 in Modena. Italy stayed
five points ahead of Slovenia, which won 2-0 at the  Faroe
Islands , in Group C.  Second-half goals from Mario Mandzukic and Ivan Klasnic
gave Croatia a 2-1 win against  Georgia  in the lone Group F game.
The win moved Croatia two points ahead of Greece, which hosts
Malta tomorrow, at the top of the standings.  The winner in each of the nine groups, along with the
second-place team with the most points, qualifies for Euro 2012
with hosts Poland and Ukraine. The remaining eight second-place
teams will play off for the final four spots.  France stayed four points ahead of Belarus in Group D when
the teams tied 1-1, while Romania beat Bosnia-Herzegovina 3-0.
Sweden won 4-1 at Moldova to move within six points of idle
Group E leader Netherlands and Finland beat San Marino 1-0.
Liechtenstein beat Lithuania 2-0 for its first win in Group I.  To contact the reporter on this story:
